Bangalore,The Organic World - Indiranagar,"12th Main, 7th Cross Rd, 7th Cross, HAL 2nd Stage, Indiranagar, Bengaluru, Karnataka 560008","https://www.google.com/maps/place/The+Organic+World+-+Indiranagar/@12.9704614,77.6450913,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x3bae172ac41b5819:0x11bcd2e9e87bcdc6!8m2!3d12.9704614!4d77.6450913!16s%2Fg%2F11frdzkd5r",4.4,0,,,,0,,"They have a lot of stuff that's organically sourced, according to the advertising. There's also a small eatery inside which I didn't try. Even though the place is fairly well stocked, it's incredibly expensive according to me. That in itself wouldn't be a problem since a place can be expensive but they have a banner outside the shop that reads ""Organic and affordable"". That felt like false advertising to me. They mostly store companies that have high priced products. I bought some spiced paneer, a jar of ghee and a couple of chocolates and incense. Apart from the incense which are from Auroville, everything was expensive. The paneer (around 200-220 gm) was around 250 rupees, the chocolates about the same and the ghee around 550 bucks. Incense was around 30 or 35. Service staff are nice.",2026-05-11 17:24:19
