Bangalore,The Organic World - Indiranagar,"12th Main, 7th Cross Rd, 7th Cross, HAL 2nd Stage, Indiranagar, Bengaluru, Karnataka 560008","https://www.google.com/maps/place/The+Organic+World+-+Indiranagar/@12.9704614,77.6450913,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x3bae172ac41b5819:0x11bcd2e9e87bcdc6!8m2!3d12.9704614!4d77.6450913!16s%2Fg%2F11frdzkd5r",4.4,0,,,,0,,"During the pandemic, my elderly parents make do with the groceries from the organic world indiranagar as they live close by. Knowing the reputation of the store, I felt somewhat comfortable with the understanding that they mostly just place the order via text message and then drive by to pick up their bags. However I was very disappointed myself when I visited the store with my mom and within a minute of being inside I saw 3 staff members not wearing masks. The ac was on, door was closed and they have around 8 - 10 staff members inside along with several customers. It felt like an unsafe environment and I ushered my mother out. I promptly told the supervisor, staff and doorman to keep their masks on and made my way out. I have advised my parents to not go inside the store anymore as the staff are not following the proper Covid safety guidelines. The quality of the vegetables is average, price is high. I admire the store concept as they have a range of lovely items and I wish them well. The staff can be helpful but you must request assistance. However the priority at this time should be the safety of their staff and customers and it appears they require some education and training on the same.",2026-05-11 17:25:23
